Decelerate

Verb

Decrease in acceleration.

Decrease, reduction, denial of influence upon acceleration.

"Throttle reduced to half, forward motion of acceleration will now decelerate to the effect."

Decelerated (past particle)

The action acceleration under gone to retain its forward motion while suppressed.

"Oh dear, well atleast the fat man decelerated himself with regards for others."

